We investigate a lot of credit card abuse cases involving cards left in wallets and purses left outside in parked vehicles. Many of those vehicles unlocked. Hundreds or thousands can be spent before the card hold realizes they've been victimized. Easy pickins for crooks.

Same for any scam ruse. Social Security, Utility companies etc. demanding immediate payment under threat of arrest. Trust us, police officers wont be standing by outside ready to arrest you if you don't make payment.

CROOKS use spoofed numbers so even if the number on caller id is the actual court number (212-0215) simply hang up and call that number yourself to verify. Officers will not be standing by outside ready to arrest you.

PHONE SCAM: Callers claiming to be from El Paso Municipal Court demanding payment at that moment to a prepaid card or face arrest at place of business or home. Hang up this is a scam. If in doubt verify at (915) 212-0215 or on line https://www.elpasotexas.gov/municipal-courts

Visit http://SoberRides.org to find alternatives to drinking alcohol and driving, such as: •Designating a sober driver •Calling a cab or ride-share service •Using mass transit •Asking a sober friend or family member for a ride •Spending the night

While drivers under the influence of alcohol risk killing or seriously injuring themselves or others, they also face up to $17,000 in fines and fees, jail time and loss of their driver’s license. EPPD and TxDOT strongly encourage everyone to plan for a sober ride
